quran[15]{c,v,t}:
  43,1,Ha-Mim
  43,2,By the clear book (the Qur’an)
  43,3,"Surely, We surely has revealed it a Qur’an in Arabic so that you may be able to understand"
  43,4,"And surely, it (this Qur’an) is in the mother of the book (Al-Lauh Al-Mahfooz) before US, indeed exalted, full of wisdom"
  43,5,Should We then take away the reminder (this Qur’an) from you in your rejection because you are a transgressing people
  43,6,And how many prophets have We sent amongst the previous people
  43,7,Never came to them a prophet and they did not mock at him
  43,8,"So We destroyed people stronger than them in power, and the example of the ancient people has passed away (before them)"
  43,9,"Indeed if you (O Muhammad) ask them: “Who has created the heavens and the earth?” They will surely say: “The All-Mighty, the All-Knower of everything created them.”"
  43,10,(Allah) Who has made the earth like a bed for you and has made roads for you in it in order that you may find your way
  43,11,"and Who sends down water (rain) from the sky in due measure. Then We revive a dead land from it, and even so you will be brought out (from the dead again)"
  43,12,and Who has created all the pairs and has appointed for you from ships and cattle on which you ride
  43,13,"in order that you may mount firmly on their backs, and then may remember the Favor of your Lord when you mount on them, and say: “Glory to Allah who has subjected this to us, and we could never have ability for it (by our efforts)"
  43,14,"and surely, to our Lord we all shall return.”"
  43,15,"Yet they assign to some of His servants a share with Him (as partners). Surely, mankind is clearly ungrateful"